---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="QR Payments - SkanPay"
  description="Learn how SkanPay frames QR code payment flows for in-store commerce, customer authorization, and merchant confirmation."
  activePath="/qr-payments/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">QR payments</p>
    <h1>A clearer scan-to-pay path for physical checkout</h1>
    <p>The transaction flow is simple to describe: request, scan, decision, and merchant result.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div class="spec-panel">
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span>Request</span>
        <p>Payment details are attached to a checkout-specific QR session.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span>Customer</span>
        <p>The customer opens the request through a supported wallet or app.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span>Decision</span>
        <p>The transaction is authorized, cancelled, expired, or left pending.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span>Merchant</span>
        <p>The checkout team needs a readable result before closing the sale.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="split-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2>The flow in plain terms</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Present the QR payment request.</li>
        <li>Open the request in a supported app or wallet.</li>
        <li>Authorize, cancel, expire, or leave the request pending.</li>
        <li>Return a readable result to the merchant.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
        <h2>QR payments can support more flexible commerce</h2>
      </div>
      <p>The value is not the code itself. The value is a checkout process that customers and staff can both understand.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid three">
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>UX</span>
        <h3>Customer familiarity</h3>
        <p>Scanning is already a common mobile action, which helps reduce explanation at the point of sale.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Partner</span>
        <h3>Wallet participation</h3>
        <p>Mobile apps and loyalty programs can participate in payment moments when the flow is clearly defined.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Store</span>
        <h3>Merchant flexibility</h3>
        <p>Stores can evaluate QR payment as an additional checkout option alongside existing acceptance methods.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
